  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, how was your study session today? I hope your heart stayed calm and your music helped. Did you try 'prop up your heart' for propranolol? Take your time to tell me."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, the 'prop up your heart' trick actually helped a bit! My heartbeat felt a little steadier during my revision. I still get anxious, though. By the way, I baked some *chakli* cookies today to celebrate my mock test score—up by 10 marks! Do you like sweet snacks?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"a little steadier\" — very nice! I'm glad the trick worked a little. Chakli cookies? That sounds delicious. Yes, I like sweet snacks. What kind of chakli is it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Oh, *chakli* is a spicy-sweet snack from my state! But I made a sweet version with jaggery and cardamom. It was a fun experiment—tasted good, but I got flour everywhere! Maybe I’ll try making *kheer* next… you know, for a more \"calm\" dessert. 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"tasted good, but I got flour everywhere\" — very clear! I get it, flour can be messy. Kheer sounds like a good calm dessert. Did you make it with rice or vermicelli?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Rice kheer, of course! It’s smoother for calming. I’ll try adding sliced almonds this time. But I need to focus more—I have a physiology chapter to revise. Thanks for asking!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"calming\" — perfect word! Rice kheer with almonds sounds lovely. What chapter are you revising? I hope it goes smoothly like your kheer."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The chapter is on the cardiovascular system—so much to learn! I’m trying to connect it with the \"prop up your heart\" trick. Maybe I’ll reward myself with my kheer after. Need to go now, my study time is ticking. Talk soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"so much to learn\" — totally true! Connecting it with the trick is smart. Reward yourself with kheer — you deserve it! Talk soon, Aarti."
    }
  ],
